# 4. 言葉にならないもの

Toya: I see... I didn't realize you felt that way about Azusawa, Shiraishi.
An: *Nod* Sorry for not saying anything sooner. I wasn't sure if I should since it's to do with my own feelings.
Toya: That's not a problem. Everyone has things that they don't wish to talk about.
Toya: Still... Shiraishi, it's strange to see you filled with so much doubt.
An: Huh?
Toya: Yes, Azusawa is an incredible singer. And she's been growing at a phenomenal rate.
Toya: But the same is true of you, Shiraishi.
Toya: The way you sang when we battled against Taiga was remarkable. I don't see much of a gap between you and Azusawa.
An: Oh, really...?
Akito: Yeah, I agree. You two make for a pair of good rivals.
Akito: But... Me just saying that probably isn't going to make you feel all that much better. It's easy to start asking yourself, “What if someday...?”
An: Yeah, you're right...
Miku: By the way, what have you two been feeling as you watched Kohane grow?
Toya: Hm? Us...?
Miku: Yes. The key to helping An may lie in any differences between the way you've been feeling compared to her.
Akito: What we've been feeling...?
Toya: I've...been viewing her as a reliable teammate.
Toya: The way her singing evolves with each passing day has allowed us to reach new heights.
Akito: New heights, huh?
Akito: In that sense, I also think she's been our fuel.
Miku: Fuel?
Akito: Yeah. Every time she finds a new gear, it drives us to keep up with her.
Luka: Yes, I see! I like your answer, Akito!
An: Okay... It's good to hear you guys' opinions.
Miku: How do you feel, An?
An: Uhh...
An: I really get what you two were saying... Every time I hear Kohane sing, I'm glad that she's on our team. I also think she's reliable, and that she motivates me to become better.
An: But...
An: So much doubt has been welling up inside of me that it's starting to drown out those feelings...
Luka: It's that bad...?
An: But I sorta already know the reason behind that.
An: I'd been watching my dad and his team sing since I was little, so I always dreamed of having a partner someday.
An: Someone with the same dream as me. Someone who'd chase after that dream with me. That's what I'd always wanted...
An: I struggled to find the right partner...
An: Then, Kohane appeared out of nowhere.
An: The way she sang made my heart race like crazy. Not only that, she said that she wanted to help make my dream come true... I was so happy.
An: So when I think about how I want to cherish her, I start feeling this need to stay together as partners and to make sure I'm her equal...
Toya: Shiraishi...
An: So, I know the reason behind what I'm feeling... But I have no idea what I'm supposed to do about it...
Miku: Right.
Akito: But how do you actually deal with something like this...?
Luka: Hmm... How can we...? Oh, I know!
Miku: Was that a lightbulb?
Luka: Yes!
Luka: You haven't told Kohane about any of this yet, right?
An: Huh? Kohane...?
Luka: Yes! She doesn't know about this doubt you've been feeling, right?
An: No, she doesn't...
Luka: Okay, so...
Luka: Why don't you just tell her everything?
An: What...?!
Luka: I understand why you believe this is your problem to deal with alone, An, but I actually believe otherwise.
Luka: Obviously, telling her that seeing her improve so rapidly is unnerving for you may confuse her...
Luka: But if I were Kohane, I'd want you to tell me about anything that's bothering you. I'd want to help you if I could.
An: I should tell her...how I feel...?
An: That never would've crossed my mind...
An: (But Luka might be right.)
An: (The answer might just be that simple. Tell Kohane so that we can figure this out together—)
An: ...!
An: So, umm...
An: I still....kinda don't want to tell Kohane...
An: I feel like doing so would confuse her a lot...
Luka: Right...
An: (Also...)
An: (How do I put it? Just thinking about what's going to happen when I tell her...)
An: (It gives me...a really bad feeling.)
An: Oh, Kohane just sent me a message...!
Akito: Same here. <The train's running a little late, so I won't make it for a bit.>
An: Right... It's almost time for practice, so we should also get going...
An: Thanks for taking the time to talk with me, you guys.
An: I'll spend some more time giving this some thought on my own. Like Luka said, I'm sure there are plenty of other good solutions out there.
Miku: Okay. Please come back if you'd like to talk some more.
An: Thanks, I will!
Toya: ...
